cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses reducing computing time and memory usage, which involves optimization techniques and machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions using a word-to-word translation model and a bilingual phrase library, which are related to language modeling and information retrieval, respectively, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) possible sub-categories.
